{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Num|24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","chapter":24,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:24:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":24,"verse":1,"text":"Since Balaam saw that it pleased the Lord to bless Israel, he did not go to seek omens as on previous occasions, but turned toward the wilderness.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:24:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":24,"verse":2,"text":"When Balaam looked up and saw Israel encamped tribe by tribe, the Spirit of God came on him,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:24:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":24,"verse":3,"text":"and he proclaimed his poem:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:24:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":24,"verse":4,"text":"the oracle of one who hears the sayings of God,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:24:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":24,"verse":5,"text":"How beautiful are your tents, Jacob,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:24:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":24,"verse":6,"text":"They stretch out like river valleys,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:24:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":24,"verse":7,"text":"Water will flow from his buckets,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:24:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":24,"verse":8,"text":"God brought him out of Egypt;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:24:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":24,"verse":9,"text":"He crouches, he lies down like a lion","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:24:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":24,"verse":10,"text":"Then Balak became furious with Balaam, struck his hands together, and said to him, “I summoned you to put a curse on my enemies, but instead, you have blessed them these three times.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:24:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":24,"verse":11,"text":"Now go to your home! I said I would reward you richly, but look, the Lord has denied you a reward.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:24:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":24,"verse":12,"text":"Balaam answered Balak, “Didn’t I previously tell the messengers you sent me:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:24:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":24,"verse":13,"text":"If Balak were to give me his house full of silver and gold, I could not go against the Lord’s command, to do anything good or bad of my own will? I will say whatever the Lord says.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:24:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":24,"verse":14,"text":"Now I am going back to my people, but first, let me warn you what these people will do to your people in the future.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:24:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":24,"verse":15,"text":"Then he proclaimed his poem:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:24:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":24,"verse":16,"text":"the oracle of one who hears the sayings of God","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:24:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":24,"verse":17,"text":"I see him, but not now;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:24:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":24,"verse":18,"text":"Edom will become a possession;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:24:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":24,"verse":19,"text":"One who comes from Jacob will rule;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:24:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":24,"verse":20,"text":"Then Balaam saw Amalek and proclaimed his poem:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:24:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":24,"verse":21,"text":"Next he saw the Kenites and proclaimed his poem:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:24:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":24,"verse":22,"text":"Kain will be destroyed","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:24:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":24,"verse":23,"text":"Once more he proclaimed his poem:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:24:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":24,"verse":24,"text":"Ships will come from the coast of Kittim;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:24:25","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapte